{"title_page": "Kara Mbodji", "text_new": "{{short description|Senegalese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Kara\n| image          = Kara Mbodj (cropped).jpg\n| caption        = Mbodji with [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in 2014\n| fullname       = Serigne Modou Kara Mbodji\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1989|11|22|df=y}}<ref name=\"FIFA\">{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia \u2013 List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF |date=4 June 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = [[Ndiass]], Senegal\n| height         = 1.92 m<ref name=\"FIFA\"/>\n| currentclub    = [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]]\n| clubnumber     = 14\n| position       = [[Centre-back]], [[defensive midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[Diambars FC]]\n| years1         = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs1         = [[Diambars FC]]\n| caps1          = 43\n| goals1         = 4\n| years2         = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs2         = [[Troms\u00f8 IL|Troms\u00f8]]\n| caps2          = 70\n| goals2         = 8\n| years3         = 2013\u20132015\n| clubs3         = [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]\n| caps3          = 75\n| goals3         = 4\n| years4         = 2015\u20132019\n| clubs4         = [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]]\n| caps4          = 91\n| goals4         = 6\n| years5         = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs5         = \u2192 [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] (loan)\n| caps5          = 6\n| goals5         = 0\n| years6         = 2019\u2013\n| clubs6         = [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]]\n| caps6          = 13\n| goals6         = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam1  = [[Senegal national under-23 football team|Senegal U23]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 7\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2011\u2013\n| nationalteam2  = [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 47\n| nationalgoals2 = 4\n| pcupdate       = 23 January 2020\n| ntupdate       = 8 June 2018\n}}\n'''Serigne Modou Kara Mbodji''' (born 22 November 1989), commonly known as '''Kara''' or '''Kara Mbodji''', is a Senegalese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]]. He can be deployed as a defender, defensive midfielder or in the central midfield.\n\n==Club career==\nAt the age of 15, Mbodji joined the Diambars academy in [[Dakar]], Senegal.<ref name=\"anderlecht\">{{cite news|title=Kara Mbodji tekent overeenkomst bij RSC Anderlecht|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20150807_01808418|accessdate=4 October 2017|work=[[Het Nieuwsblad]]|date=7 August 2015|language=Dutch}}</ref> On 2 February 2010, he joined Norwegian club [[Troms\u00f8 IL]]. During his three seasons in the [[Norwegian Premier League]], he was awarded best player of his team and twice second best player of the Championship.\n\nOn 31 December 2012, Mbodji joined [[KRC Genk]] for a fee of \u20ac1.4 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://fotball.aftenposten.no/eliteserien/article255809.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Kara enig med Genk |publisher=Aftenposten |date=31 October 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102014933/http://fotball.aftenposten.no/eliteserien/article255809.ece |archivedate=2 November 2012 }}</ref> After regularly starting for Genk in defence and winning the [[2012\u201313 Belgian Cup]], his contract was extended until June 2018.\n\nOn 7 August 2015, he joined [[R.S.C. Anderlecht]] for a fee of \u20ac4.5 million, signing a four-year deal until June 2019.<ref name=\"anderlecht\"/> In August 2017, he agreed a contract extension with the club until 2020.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dove|first1=Ed|title=Kara Mbodji extends Anderlecht deal|url=http://www.espnfc.com/anderlecht/story/3178660/kara-mbodji-extends-anderlecht-deal|accessdate=4 October 2017|work=ESPN FC|date=13 August 2017}}</ref> In his time at the club he made 97 appearances scoring 7 goals.<ref name=\"nantes\">{{cite news |last1=Okeleji |first1=Oluwashina |title=Senegal's Kara Mbodji joins Nantes on season's loan |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45353582 |accessdate=31 August 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=30 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 August 2018, one day before the closing of the 2018 summer transfer window, Mbodji moved to [[Ligue 1]] side [[FC Nantes]] on loan for the 2018\u201319 season. Nantes also secured an option to sign him permanently.<ref name=\"nantes\"/> His loan ended early, in January 2019, with Mbodji citing lack of playing time.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Okeleji |first1=Oluwashina |title=Senegal's Kara Mbodji confirms and explains Nantes exit |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/46876312 |accessdate=16 January 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=15 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 July 2019, [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]] signed Kara Mbodji for three season from Anderlecht.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kara Mbodji (ex-Nantes) quitte Anderlecht pour Al-Sailiya |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Kara-mbodji-ex-nantes-quitte-anderlecht-pour-al-sailiya/1042007 |website=L'\u00c9quipe |language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nMbodji was a part of the [[Senegal national under-23 football team|Senegal]] team for the [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics&nbsp;\u2013 Men's tournament|2012 Olympic Games]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/mb/kara-mbodj-1.html|title=Kara Mbodj Bio, Stats, and Results|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> He was included in the [[Senegal national football team]]'s squad for the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]] and scored in a 1\u20131 draw with [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]] in the team's second group match.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30843618|title=South Africa 1-1 Senegal|accessdate=24 January 2015|work=BBC}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018 he was named in Senegal\u2019s 23-man squad for the [[2018 World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Crawford |first1=Stephen |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb |website=Goal |accessdate=16 July 2019 |date=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 8 January 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Troms\u00f8 IL|Troms\u00f8]]\n|[[2010 Tippeligaen|2010]]<ref name=\"KMSW\">{{soccerway|122768|accessdate=22 July 2017}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Eliteserien (football)|Tippeligaen]]\n|22||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||24||0\n|-\n|[[2011 Tippeligaen|2011]]<ref name=\"KMSW\" />\n|26||5||1||0||4<ref group=lower-alpha name=\"UEL\">Appearances in the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]</ref>||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||31||5\n|-\n|[[2012 Tippeligaen|2012]]<ref name=KM11>{{soccerbase season|59161|2011|accessdate=22 July 2017}}</ref>\n|22||3||4||0||3<ref group=lower-alpha name=\"UEL\" />||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||29||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!70||8||7||0||7||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||84||9\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Belgian Pro League|2012\u201313]]<ref name=\"wf\">{{cite web |title=Serigne Mbodj \u00bb Club matches |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/serigne-mbodj/2/ |website=worldfootball.net |accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"KM12\">{{soccerbase season|59161|2012|accessdate=22 July 2017}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Belgian First Division A|Pro League]]\n|